    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the onion is softened, add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> to the pot with your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, the <strong>remaining curry powder</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up, season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1667320649629-x200.jpg",
