            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>red lentils</strong> with 650ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[850ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1.1L]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>and your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>to the pot and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook covered for 15-20 min or until the lentils and carrot have softened</p><p>Once softened, remove the pot from the heat and blitz with a <strong>(stick) blender</strong> until smooth, then return to a low heat to keep warm – this is your <strong>curried lentil soup</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1667320652588-x200.jpg",
