            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong> in a bowl with a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>– this is your <strong>garlic oil</strong></p><p>Discard the <strong>tin foil</strong>,<strong> </strong>then add your <strong>roti </strong>to the reserved baking tray[s]</p><p>Spread your <strong>garlic oil </strong>over the <strong>roti </strong>until evenly coated</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 3-4 min or until warmed through – these are your <strong>garlic roti</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
